{"content":[{"data":{"color":"black","source":"The Preacher","time_period":["0s AD"],"unique_sources":["The Preacher","Unknown","Apollos","Barnabas","Priscilla"]},"nodes":[{"type":"prose","nodes":[{"marks":[{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"19"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"\t"},{"marks":[{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"19"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"chapter"}],"object":"leaf","text":"10"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"19"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"19"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"19"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And so, dear brothers and sisters,* we can boldly enter heaven’s Most Holy Place because of the blood of Jesus. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"20"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"20"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"20"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"By his death,* Jesus opened a new and life-giving way through the curtain into the Most Holy Place. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"21"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"21"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"21"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And since we have a great High Priest who rules over God’s house, "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"22"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"22"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"22"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"let us go right into the presence of God with sincere hearts fully trusting him. For our guilty consciences have been sprinkled with Christ’s blood to make us clean, and our bodies have been washed with pure water. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"23"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"23"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"23"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Let us hold tightly without wavering to the hope we affirm, for God can be trusted to keep his promise. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"24"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"24"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"24"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Let us think of ways to motivate one another to acts of love and good works. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"25"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"25"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"25"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And let us not neglect our meeting together, as some people do, but encourage one another, especially now that the day of his return is drawing near. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"26"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"26"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"26"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Dear friends, if we deliberately continue sinning after we have received knowledge of the truth, there is no longer any sacrifice that will cover these sins. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"27"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"27"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"27"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"There is only the terrible expectation of God’s judgment and the raging fire that will consume his enemies. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"28"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"28"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"28"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"For anyone who refused to obey the law of Moses was put to death without mercy on the testimony of two or three witnesses. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"29"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"29"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"29"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Just think how much worse the punishment will be for those who have trampled on the Son of God, and have treated the blood of the covenant, which made us holy, as if it were common and unholy, and have insulted and disdained the Holy Spirit who brings God’s mercy to us. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"30"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"For we know the one who said,\n"}]},{"type":"poetry","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"}],"object":"leaf","text":"“I will take revenge. \nI will pay them back.”*"}]},{"type":"prose","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"He also said,\n"}]},{"type":"poetry","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"}],"object":"leaf","text":"“The Lord will judge his own people.”* "}]},{"type":"prose","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":""},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"31"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"31"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"31"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It is a terrible thing to fall into the hands of the living God. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"32"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"32"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"32"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Think back on those early days when you first learned about Christ.* Remember how you remained faithful even though it meant terrible suffering. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"33"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"33"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"33"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Sometimes you were exposed to public ridicule and were beaten, and sometimes you helped others who were suffering the same things. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"34"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"34"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"34"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"You suffered along with those who were thrown into jail, and when all you owned was taken from you, you accepted it with joy. You knew there were better things waiting for you that will last forever. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"35"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"35"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"35"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"So do not throw away this confident trust in the Lord. Remember the great reward it brings you! "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"36"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"36"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"36"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Patient endurance is what you need now, so that you will continue to do God’s will. Then you will receive all that he has promised. \n"}]},{"type":"poetry","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"37"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"37"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"37"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"“For in just a little while, \nthe Coming One will come and not delay. \n"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"38"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"38"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"38"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And my righteous ones will live by faith.* \nBut I will take no pleasure in anyone who turns away.”* "}]},{"type":"prose","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"38"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":""},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"39"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"39"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"10","verse":"39"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"But we are not like those who turn away from God to their own destruction. We are the faithful ones, whose souls will be saved. "},{"marks":[{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"\n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"chapter"}],"object":"leaf","text":"11"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"1"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Faith is the confidence that what we hope for will actually happen; it gives us assurance about things we cannot see. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"2"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"2"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"2"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Through their faith, the people in days of old earned a good reputation. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"3"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"3"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"3"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"By faith we understand that the entire universe was formed at God’s command, that what we now see did not come from anything that can be seen. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"4"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"4"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"4"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Abel brought a more acceptable offering to God than Cain did. Abel’s offering gave evidence that he was a righteous man, and God showed his approval of his gifts. Although Abel is long dead, he still speaks to us by his example of faith. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"5"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"5"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"5"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Enoch was taken up to heaven without dying—“he disappeared, because God took him.”* For before he was taken up, he was known as a person who pleased God. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"6"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"6"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"6"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And it is impossible to please God without faith. Anyone who wants to come to him must believe that God exists and that he rewards those who sincerely seek him. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"7"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"7"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"7"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Noah built a large boat to save his family from the flood. He obeyed God, who warned him about things that had never happened before. By his faith Noah condemned the rest of the world, and he received the righteousness that comes by faith. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"8"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"8"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"8"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Abraham obeyed when God called him to leave home and go to another land that God would give him as his inheritance. He went without knowing where he was going. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"9"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"9"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"9"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And even when he reached the land God promised him, he lived there by faith—for he was like a foreigner, living in tents. And so did Isaac and Jacob, who inherited the same promise. "},{"marks":[{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"10"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"10"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"10"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Abraham was confidently looking forward to a city with eternal foundations, a city designed and built by God. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"11"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"11"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"11"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that even Sarah was able to have a child, though she was barren and was too old. She believed* that God would keep his promise. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"12"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"12"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"12"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And so a whole nation came from this one man who was as good as dead—a nation with so many people that, like the stars in the sky and the sand on the seashore, there is no way to count them. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"13"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"13"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"13"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"All these people died still believing what God had promised them. They did not receive what was promised, but they saw it all from a distance and welcomed it. They agreed that they were foreigners and nomads here on earth. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"14"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"14"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"14"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Obviously people who say such things are looking forward to a country they can call their own. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"15"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"15"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"15"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"If they had longed for the country they came from, they could have gone back. "},{"marks":[{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"16"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"16"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"16"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"But they were looking for a better place, a heavenly homeland. That is why God is not ashamed to be called their God, for he has prepared a city for them. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"17"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"},{"data":{"id":"REL-08"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"17"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"17"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"data":{"id":"REL-08"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Abraham offered Isaac as a sacrifice when God was testing him. Abraham, who had received God’s promises, was ready to sacrifice his only son, Isaac, "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"18"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"},{"data":{"id":"REL-08"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"18"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"18"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"data":{"id":"REL-08"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"even though God had told him, “Isaac is the son through whom your descendants will be counted.”* "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"19"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"},{"data":{"id":"REL-08"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"19"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"19"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"data":{"id":"REL-08"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Abraham reasoned that if Isaac died, God was able to bring him back to life again. And in a sense, Abraham did receive his son back from the dead."},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"19"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":" \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"20"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"20"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"20"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Isaac promised blessings for the future to his sons, Jacob and Esau. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"21"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"21"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"21"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Jacob, when he was old and dying, blessed each of Joseph’s sons and bowed in worship as he leaned on his staff. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"22"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"22"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"22"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Joseph, when he was about to die, said confidently that the people of Israel would leave Egypt. He even commanded them to take his bones with them when they left. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"23"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"23"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"23"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Moses’ parents hid him for three months when he was born. They saw that God had given them an unusual child, and they were not afraid to disobey the king’s command. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"24"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"24"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"24"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Moses, when he grew up, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh’s daughter. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"25"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"25"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"25"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"He chose to share the oppression of God’s people instead of enjoying the fleeting pleasures of sin. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"26"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"26"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"26"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"He thought it was better to suffer for the sake of Christ than to own the treasures of Egypt, for he was looking ahead to his great reward. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"27"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"27"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"27"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Moses left the land of Egypt, not fearing the king’s anger. He kept right on going because he kept his eyes on the one who is invisible. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"28"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"28"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"28"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Moses commanded the people of Israel to keep the Passover and to sprinkle blood on the doorposts so that the angel of death would not kill their firstborn sons. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"29"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"29"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"29"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that the people of Israel went right through the Red Sea as though they were on dry ground. But when the Egyptians tried to follow, they were all drowned. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"30"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"30"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that the people of Israel marched around Jericho for seven days, and the walls came crashing down. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"31"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"31"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"31"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"It was by faith that Rahab the prostitute was not destroyed with the people in her city who refused to obey God. For she had given a friendly welcome to the spies. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"32"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"32"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"32"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"How much more do I need to say? It would take too long to recount the stories of the faith of Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, David, Samuel, and all the prophets. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"33"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"33"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"33"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"By faith these people overthrew kingdoms, ruled with justice, and received what God had promised them. They shut the mouths of lions, "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"34"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"34"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"34"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"quenched the flames of fire, and escaped death by the edge of the sword. Their weakness was turned to strength. They became strong in battle and put whole armies to flight. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"35"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"35"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"35"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Women received their loved ones back again from death.\n\tBut others were tortured, refusing to turn from God in order to be set free. They placed their hope in a better life after the resurrection. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"36"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"36"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"36"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Some were jeered at, and their backs were cut open with whips. Others were chained in prisons. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"37"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"37"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"37"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Some died by stoning, some were sawed in half,* and others were killed with the sword. Some went about wearing skins of sheep and goats, destitute and oppressed and mistreated. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"38"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"38"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"38"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"They were too good for this world, wandering over deserts and mountains, hiding in caves and holes in the ground. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"39"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"39"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"39"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"All these people earned a good reputation because of their faith, yet none of them received all that God had promised. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"40"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"40"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"11","verse":"40"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"For God had something better in mind for us, so that they would not reach perfection without us. "},{"marks":[{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"\n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"chapter"},{"data":{"id":"CEL-07"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"12"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"},{"data":{"id":"CEL-07"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"1"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"1"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"data":{"id":"CEL-07"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Therefore, since we are surrounded by such a huge crowd of witnesses to the life of faith, let us strip off every weight that slows us down, especially the sin that so easily trips us up. And let us run with endurance the race God has set before us. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"},{"data":{"id":"CEL-07"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"2"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"2"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"2"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"data":{"id":"CEL-07"},"object":"mark","type":"keyPassage"}],"object":"leaf","text":"We do this by keeping our eyes on Jesus, the champion who initiates and perfects our faith.* Because of the joy* awaiting him, he endured the cross, disregarding its shame. Now he is seated in the place of honor beside God’s throne."},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"2"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":" "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"3"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"3"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"3"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Think of all the hostility he endured from sinful people;* then you won’t become weary and give up. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"4"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"4"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"4"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"After all, you have not yet given your lives in your struggle against sin. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"5"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"5"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"5"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"And have you forgotten the encouraging words God spoke to you as his children?* He said, \n"}]},{"type":"poetry","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"5"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"}],"object":"leaf","text":"“My child,* don’t make light of the Lord’s discipline, \nand don’t give up when he corrects you. \n"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"6"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"6"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"object":"mark","type":"poetry"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"6"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"For the Lord disciplines those he loves, \nand he punishes each one he accepts as his child.”* "}]},{"type":"prose","nodes":[{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"6"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":""},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"7"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"7"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"7"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"As you endure this divine discipline, remember that God is treating you as his own children. Who ever heard of a child who is never disciplined by its father? "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"8"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"8"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"8"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"If God doesn’t discipline you as he does all of his children, it means that you are illegitimate and are not really his children at all. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"9"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"9"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"9"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Since we respected our earthly fathers who disciplined us, shouldn’t we submit even more to the discipline of the Father of our spirits, and live forever?* \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"10"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"10"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"10"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"For our earthly fathers disciplined us for a few years, doing the best they knew how. But God’s discipline is always good for us, so that we might share in his holiness. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"11"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"11"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"11"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"No discipline is enjoyable while it is happening—it’s painful! But afterward there will be a peaceful harvest of right living for those who are trained in this way. \n\t"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"12"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"12"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"12"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"So take a new grip with your tired hands and strengthen your weak knees. "},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"13"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"},{"object":"mark","type":"verse"}],"object":"leaf","text":"13"},{"marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"literature"},{"data":{"book":"Heb","chapter":"12","verse":"13"},"object":"mark","type":"reference"}],"object":"leaf","text":"Mark out a straight path for your feet so that those who are weak and lame will not fall but become strong. \n\t"}]}]}],"colors":{"total":1963,"black":1963,"red":0,"green":0,"blue":0},"repeatedWords":["God (33)","us (19)","faith (29)","people (15)","have (11)","had (10)","all (10)","God’s (9)","those (8)","our (8)","promised (7)","back (6)","without (6)","good (6)","Abraham (6)","discipline (6)","received (6)","even (6)","Isaac (6)","own (5)"],"sources":{"The Preacher":{"words":1963,"color":"black"}},"id":"S350"}